{
  "episodeId": "HuFR5XBYLfU",
  "channelSlug": "@teded",
  "title": "How is power divided in the United States government? - Belinda Stutzman",
  "publishedAt": "2013-04-12T17:26:31.000Z",
  "rawLines": [
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Translator: Andrea McDonough\nReviewer: Bedirhan Cinar",
      "offset": 0,
      "duration": 7
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Have you ever wondered",
      "offset": 14.259,
      "duration": 1.247
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "who has the authority to make laws",
      "offset": 15.506,
      "duration": 1.792
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "or punish people who break them?",
      "offset": 17.298,
      "duration": 1.96
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "When we think of power in the United States,",
      "offset": 19.258,
      "duration": 2.255
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "we usually think of the President,",
      "offset": 21.513,
      "duration": 1.716
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "but he does not act alone.",
      "offset": 23.229,
      "duration": 1.685
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "In fact, he is only one piece of the power puzzle",
      "offset": 24.914,
      "duration": 3.022
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and for very good reason.",
      "offset": 27.936,
      "duration": 1.888
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "When the American Revolution ended in 1783,",
      "offset": 29.824,
      "duration": 2.998
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "the United States government was in a state of change.",
      "offset": 32.822,
      "duration": 2.661
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "The founding fathers knew",
      "offset": 35.483,
      "duration": 1.585
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "that they did not want to establish another country",
      "offset": 37.068,
      "duration": 2.185
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "that was ruled by a king,",
      "offset": 39.253,
      "duration": 1.533
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "so the discussions were centered on",
      "offset": 40.786,
      "duration": 1.885
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "having a strong and fair national government",
      "offset": 42.671,
      "duration": 2.324
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "that protected individual freedoms",
      "offset": 44.995,
      "duration": 2.004
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and did not abuse its power.",
      "offset": 46.999,
      "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "When the new constitution was adopted in 1787,",
      "offset": 49.499,
      "duration": 3.178
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "the structure of the infant government of the United States",
      "offset": 52.677,
      "duration": 2.659
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "called for three separate branches,",
      "offset": 55.336,
      "duration": 2.254
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "each with their own powers,",
      "offset": 57.59,
      "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and a system of checks and balances.",
      "offset": 59.03,
      "duration": 2.477
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "This would ensure that no one branch",
      "offset": 61.507,
      "duration": 1.795
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "would ever become too powerful",
      "offset": 63.302,
      "duration": 1.67
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "because the other branches would always be able",
      "offset": 64.972,
      "duration": 2.003
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "to check the power of the other two.",
      "offset": 66.975,
      "duration": 2.132
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "These branches work together to run the country",
      "offset": 69.107,
      "duration": 2.289
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and set guidelines for us all to live by.",
      "offset": 71.396,
      "duration": 2.377
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "The legislative branch is described in Article 1 of the U.S. Constitution.",
      "offset": 73.773,
      "duration": 3.88
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Many people feel that the founding fathers",
      "offset": 77.653,
      "duration": 2.168
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "put this branch in the document first",
      "offset": 79.821,
      "duration": 2.031
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "because they thought it was the most important.",
      "offset": 81.852,
      "duration": 2.304
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "The legislative branch is comprised of",
      "offset": 84.156,
      "duration": 2.14
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "100 U.S. Senators",
      "offset": 86.296,
      "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and 435 members in the U.S. House of Representatives.",
      "offset": 87.996,
      "duration": 3.67
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "This is better known as the U.S. Congress.",
      "offset": 91.666,
      "duration": 2.665
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Making laws is the primary function of the legislative branch,",
      "offset": 94.331,
      "duration": 3.591
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "but it is also responsible for",
      "offset": 97.922,
      "duration": 2.166
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "approving federal judges and justices,",
      "offset": 100.088,
      "duration": 1.928
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "passing the national budget,",
      "offset": 102.016,
      "duration": 1.62
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and declaring war.",
      "offset": 103.636,
      "duration": 2.169
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Each state gets two Senators",
      "offset": 105.805,
      "duration": 1.752
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and some number of Representatives,",
      "offset": 107.557,
      "duration": 1.626
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "depending on how many people live in that state.",
      "offset": 109.183,
      "duration": 2.913
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "The executive branch is described in Article 2 of the Constitution.",
      "offset": 112.096,
      "duration": 3.678
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "The leaders of this branch of government",
      "offset": 115.774,
      "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "are the President and Vice President,",
      "offset": 117.674,
      "duration": 1.811
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "who are responsible for enforcing the laws",
      "offset": 119.485,
      "duration": 2.068
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "that Congress sets forth.",
      "offset": 121.553,
      "duration": 1.603
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "The President works closely with a group of advisors,",
      "offset": 123.156,
      "duration": 2.14
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "known as the Cabinet.",
      "offset": 125.296,
      "duration": 1.41
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "These appointed helpers assist the President",
      "offset": 126.706,
      "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "in making important decisions within their area of expertise,",
      "offset": 128.546,
      "duration": 3.342
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "such as defense,",
      "offset": 131.888,
      "duration": 0.962
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "the treasury,",
      "offset": 132.85,
      "duration": 1.084
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and homeland security.",
      "offset": 133.934,
      "duration": 1.818
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "The executive branch also appoints government officials,",
      "offset": 135.752,
      "duration": 3.224
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "commands the armed forces,",
      "offset": 138.976,
      "duration": 1.572
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and meets with leaders of other nations.",
      "offset": 140.548,
      "duration": 2.751
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "All that combined is a lot of work for a lot of people.",
      "offset": 143.299,
      "duration": 3.055
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "In fact, the executive branch employs",
      "offset": 146.354,
      "duration": 2.085
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "over 4 million people to get everything done.",
      "offset": 148.439,
      "duration": 3.328
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "The third brand of the U.S. government is the judicial branch",
      "offset": 151.767,
      "duration": 3.028
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and is detailed in Article 3.",
      "offset": 154.795,
      "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "This branch is comprised of all the courts in the land,",
      "offset": 156.715,
      "duration": 2.769
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "from the federal district courts",
      "offset": 159.484,
      "duration": 1.541
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "to the U.S. Supreme Court.",
      "offset": 161.025,
      "duration": 1.799
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "These courts interpret our nation's laws",
      "offset": 162.824,
      "duration": 1.63
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and punish those who break them.",
      "offset": 164.454,
      "duration": 1.787
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "The highest court, the Supreme Court,",
      "offset": 166.241,
      "duration": 2.139
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "settles disputes among states,",
      "offset": 168.38,
      "duration": 1.897
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "hears appeals from state and federal courts,",
      "offset": 170.277,
      "duration": 2.275
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and determines if federal laws are constitutional.",
      "offset": 172.552,
      "duration": 2.903
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "There are nine justices on the Supreme Court,",
      "offset": 175.455,
      "duration": 2.636
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and, unlike any other job in our government,",
      "offset": 178.091,
      "duration": 2.123
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Supreme Court justices are appointed for life,",
      "offset": 180.214,
      "duration": 2.669
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "or for as long as they want to stay.",
      "offset": 182.883,
      "duration": 2.293
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Our democracy depends on an informed citizenry,",
      "offset": 185.176,
      "duration": 2.956
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "so it is our duty to know how it works",
      "offset": 188.132,
      "duration": 2.008
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and what authority each branch of government has",
      "offset": 190.14,
      "duration": 2.335
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "over its citizens.",
      "offset": 192.475,
      "duration": 1.207
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "Besides voting,",
      "offset": 193.682,
      "duration": 1.129
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "chances are that some time in your life",
      "offset": 194.811,
      "duration": 1.918
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "you'll be called upon to participate in your government,",
      "offset": 196.729,
      "duration": 2.626
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "whether it is to serve on a jury,",
      "offset": 199.355,
      "duration": 1.796
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "testify in court,",
      "offset": 201.151,
      "duration": 1.21
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "or petition your Congress person",
      "offset": 202.361,
      "duration": 1.832
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "to pass or defeat an idea for a law.",
      "offset": 204.193,
      "duration": 2.518
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "By knowning the branches,",
      "offset": 206.711,
      "duration": 1.144
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "who runs them,",
      "offset": 207.855,
      "duration": 0.863
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and how they work together,",
      "offset": 208.718,
      "duration": 1.275
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "you can be involved,",
      "offset": 209.993,
      "duration": 1.084
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "informed,",
      "offset": 211.077,
      "duration": 0.835
    },
    {
      "lang": "en",
      "text": "and intelligent.",
      "offset": 211.912,
      "duration": 1.668
    }
  ],
  "cleanText": null,
  "dumpedAt": "2025-07-21T18:43:24.371Z"
}